<TITLE> JMB men get 39 years for serial bombings </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Netrokona, Oct 12 (bdnews24.com)A court has convicted four Jama'atul Mujahideen Bangladesh militants of the series bomb attacks in Aug 2005 in Netrokona and jailed them each to 39 years on Monday. The convicts are chief of the banned Islamist outfit Shayekh Abdur Rahman (death convict executed in another case), regional commander Kawsar Ahmed Younus (absconding), Kawsar Alam Sumon and Amanullah alias Sanaullah. Additional district and sessions judge Ekramul Huq Chowdhury delivered the verdict under section 3 and 4 of the Explosives Act of 1908 and under 15(3) of Special Powers Act of 1974 after taking the deposition of witnesses. The brief case details say aiming to establish Islamic rule in the country, JMB members on Aug 17, 2005 carried out synchronised bomb attacks on the Netrokona District Judge's Court premises, deputy commissioner's office premises, Super Market, Government College, Rajur Bazar and Hosenpur inter-district bus terminal. Monwar Hossain, sub-inspector of Sadar Police Station, filed the case on Aug 18, 2005. Sub-inspector Alauddin pressed the charges against the four on Nov 27, 2007. bdne
